article.headline: Dartmouth 74, James Madison 70
article.story: HARRISONBURG, Va. (AP) -- Alex Barnett scored 13 points and grabbed 12 rebounds to lead Dartmouth to a 74-70 victory Sunday over James Madison and their first win of the season. The Big Green (1-6) took the lead early with a three-pointer from Leon Pattman to make it 11-7. A jumper by James Madison's Kyle Swanston kicked off a four-basket run that put the Dukes ahead 15-11, their largest lead. Dartmouth led at halftime 36-23, and James Madison (2-6) was unable to regain the advantage. A three-pointer by Colbey Santos with seconds to go put James Madison within four points, but time ran out. Jonathan Ball scored 16 points for Dartmouth; Pattman scored 15. Juwann James and Pierre Curtis each scored 15 points to lead the Dukes, and Santos scored 14.
